Package org.prebake.js

Primitives for JSON and YSON serialization and deserialization, and plumbing that defines the environment in which user JavaScript runs.

See:
          Description

Interface Summary
Interface Description
Executor Abstracts away execution of script.
JsonSerializable A JavaScript object that can be serialized to JSON.
Loader Invokable from JavaScript to load another JavaScript module.
MembranableFunction Marker interface for a function that can pass across the JavaScript membrane to be exposed as an object.
MembranableList Marker interface for a list that can pass across the JavaScript membrane to be exposed as an array-like object.
MembranableMap Marker interface for a map that can pass across the JavaScript membrane to be exposed as an object.
MembranableMethod A placeholder interface to indicate that a method should get the this value as its zero-th argument.
ScriptableSkeleton The specification of an object that can be created once we have a JavaScript context to run it in.
YSONConverter<T> A schema for converting and checking the output of script execution.

Exception Description

Package org.prebake.js Description

Primitives for JSON and YSON serialization and deserialization, and plumbing that defines the environment in which user JavaScript runs. See the wiki docs for the tool file environment and the plan file environment.
